        <h2>Why we exist</h2>
        <p>
          Every ambitious project — a tower, a bridge, a campus, a corridor — rests on
          measurements that have to be right. Yet the people who can capture that ground truth,
          the licensed engineering firms and the certified pilots flying LiDAR and photogrammetry
          missions, spend too much of their time chasing leads instead of doing the work.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>AirXSpatial</strong> closes that gap. We are the marketplace for engineering and
          survey — the sales-and-marketing layer that routes qualified, in-scope work to the firms
          and pilots best equipped to deliver it.
        </p>

        <h2>What we do</h2>
        <p>
          Developers, general contractors, and asset owners publish what a site needs measured —
          a boundary survey, a façade inspection, a LiDAR capture, a construction-progress mission.
          AirXSpatial matches that scope to credentialed firms and certified pilots, who bid and
          deliver survey-grade results documented to the standards the project answers to.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Surveying &amp; geomatics</strong> — boundary, topographic, and as-built work</li>
          <li><strong>Inspection &amp; compliance</strong> — structural, façade, and infrastructure</li>
          <li><strong>LiDAR &amp; point clouds</strong> — aerial and terrestrial, registered to survey grade</li>
          <li><strong>Photogrammetry &amp; 3D</strong> — orthomosaics, meshes, and digital twins</li>
          <li><strong>Construction progress</strong> — repeat captures tracked against plan</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <p>
          Trust is the product. Every firm and pilot in the network is credentialed and insured,
          and every delivery builds a verifiable track record. We hold the marketplace to a simple
          standard: the people who measure twice should win the work.
        </p>

        <h2>Where we’re headed</h2>
        <p>
          Today, AirXSpatial is focused on building the network and the trust behind it. As demand
          grows, the marketplace opens into a full bidding platform — but the principle stays the
          same: ground truth, delivered by the right people, wherever the work is.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
